Access modifiers are essential tools that define how the 
members of a class, like variables, methods, and even the 
class itself, can be accessed from other parts of our program.

> private
* code
class Person{
    private String name;

    public void setName(String name){
        this.name = name;
    }

    public String getName(){
        return name;
    }
}

public class program2{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Person p = new Person();
        //p.setName("Rishi");

        System.out.println(p.getName());
    }
}

